The paper deals with the optimization of interleavers for turbo codes, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network communications (cs.NI). The use of Garello's method, which is a technique for determining the distance spectra of interleavers, suggests that the paper may also be relevant to signal processing (cs.SI). The search for good interleavers involves a computational optimization problem, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to computer communications (cs.CC) as it deals with the performance of error-correcting codes in communication systems.
